        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30981",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Jeffrey,\nWhat do you mean by \"causes things to fail\"? What is the failure you're experiencing?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-14T14:06:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-14T14:06:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30984",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've created a new Zend_Gdata object, let's call it My_Gdata_App\n\nI've registered My_Gdata_App however when I use the newAppEntry method, which is processed by a magic __ method in Zend_Gdata, it attempts to load the My_Gdata_App _Entry object from various places. The problem occurs when it checks to see if my extension exists. The class_exists() call invokes the autoloader automatically so I end up with a Zend_Loader::include() error (for My\/Gdata\/App\/Extension\/Entry.php) because it can't find the file it was looking for. Not finding it was the expected result since the correct path is in the second loop (My\/Gdata\/App\/Entry.php), but it can't loop since it failed in the first loop.\n\nBasically the if statement itself creates a situation where the code in the brackets will never run since the class_exists will trigger the Zend_Loader to try and load the file to see if it exists. You just need to add the \"false\" as the second argment to prevent class_exists from invoking autoloading, then your code will load it as necessary. \n\noh, and ignore the echo 'test'; bit in the original bug, that was me to see if the if statement ever executed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jeffrey",
                        "name": "jeffrey",
                        "displayName": "Jeffrey Sambells",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-14T15:37:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-14T15:37:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32131",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed for trunk in r16265.\n\n{noformat}\ncommit 6e759f924cf239eff23a33d4e31d9e89d1eb0a6b\nAuthor: tjohns <tjohns@44c647ce-9c0f-0410-b52a-842ac1e357ba>\nDate:   Wed Jun 24 01:15:52 2009 +0000\n\n    ZF-6660: Disable class_exists() autoloader in Zend_Gdata_App::__call() and\n    Zend_Gdata_Gapps::__call() for compatibility with magic factories.\n    \n    This corrects a bug that was introduced by r15576.\n    \n    Found by: jeffrey (Jeffrey Sambells)\n    \n    git-svn-id: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/svn\/framework\/standard\/trunk@16265 44c647ce-9c0f-0410-b52a-842ac1e357ba\n\n library\/Zend\/Gdata\/App.php   |    4 +++-\n library\/Zend\/Gdata\/Gapps.php |    4 +++-\n 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-23T18:17:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-23T18:17:36.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
